-- Obama to hold Ebola meeting at White House, postpones trip
-- 
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 12:13PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Oct 15 (Reuters) - U.S. President Barack Obama abruptly postponed a political trip he was to make on Wednesday to stay at the White House to convene a high-level meeting about the Ebola outbreak.

The White House said Obama's trip to New Jersey and Connecticut has been postponed. "Later this afternoon, the president will convene a meeting at the White House of his team coordinating the government's response to the Ebola outbreak," spokesman Josh Earnest said.